# Persona Report Template

## 🚨 Rules of use (read first)

**The only correct way to produce an HTML report is to call the `render_persona_report` tool.**

The tool automatically handles:
- Computing 55 D scalars from sections data (message stats, MBTI axes, intimacy dims, chart data, etc.)
- Generating 27 HTML fragments from sections data (28-dim deep analysis, 10 theatre acts, 20 quotes, etc.)
- Reading template.html + strings.json for template substitution
- Validating DOM element counts
- Writing the final HTML file

### ❌ Forbidden

1. **Do NOT generate D scalars or HTML fragments yourself** — the tool auto-generates them.
2. **Do NOT Read template.html / strings.json** — the tool reads them.
3. **Do NOT emit large HTML strings in your response to Write** — the tool writes the file.
4. **Do NOT write `.py` / `.js` / `.ps1` / `.sh` scripts** to process the template.
5. **Do NOT use file_operation to write an HTML report** — call render_persona_report.

### ✅ Correct flow

```
1. analyze_agent_history(action="analyze_all")        # if not analyzed
2. analyze_agent_history(action="extract_sections")   # produces sections + stats, cached to disk
3. render_persona_report({
     sections: <sections object from extract_sections>,
     stats: <stats object from extract_sections>
   })
4. Report: tool's returned file path + size + validation result
```

### 🛟 Fallback flow (if you lose the sections object)

If your `extract_sections` response got truncated or you can no longer reference the `sections`/`stats` objects, **call `render_persona_report` with no arguments**. The tool will auto-load the latest `sections` + `stats` from the extract_sections cache on disk and render from there. The response will say `Source: sections auto-loaded from extract_sections cache`.

You must still have run `extract_sections` first — the cache is what that step writes.

### 📁 Output path

- If the user has set an AI Doc folder (DoCPath), the report is written to `<DoCPath>/<AgentName>_report.html` — visible to the user alongside their notes.
- If DoCPath is empty, the tool falls back to `<dataPath>/agent-artifacts/agents/<agentId>.report.html` (internal).

You don't need to move the file yourself — the tool writes to the right place.

---

## Tool parameters

| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `sections` | object | ⚠️ Recommended | The sections object from extract_sections (19 keys). Omit to auto-load from cache. |
| `stats` | object | No | The stats object from extract_sections. Omit to auto-load from cache. |
| `agent_name` | string | No | Override agent display name; default: context.agentName |
| `language_override` | string | No | `"zh"` or `"en"` to override language setting |

### The 19 section keys

`persona_card` · `dialogue_theatre` · `subtext_decoder` · `interaction_tips` · `topic_preferences` · `signals` · `best_communication_times` · `expected_next` · `trajectory` · `character_portrait` · `surprising_contradiction` · `compatibility` · `key_quotes` · `gift_suggestions` · `health_index` · `growth_suggestions` · `ocean` · `mbti` · `attachment`

### Stats object fields

`total_messages` · `date_range {first, last}` · `senders {name: count}` · `monthly_activity {"YYYY-MM": count}` · `avg_message_length`

---

## Design language (baked into template CSS — untouchable)

Warm cream editorial — Coral `#CC785C` + Forest green `#3B6E6A` + Amber `#B57E3A` + Cream `#F0E9DD`. Serif headings + sans body.

**Your job is not visuals** — just pass sections + stats data; the tool handles everything.

---

## What the tool auto-generates

All of the following are computed/generated internally from sections/stats data. **You do NOT provide these:**

### 55 D scalars (auto-computed)
- Message stats: totals, sender counts, percentages, avg length
- Time span: years, first/last year, peak year
- Intimacy 5 dimensions: total, trust, dependency, density, depth, stability
- Chemistry triplet, zodiac quadruplet
- MBTI type + 4 axis percentages + dominant labels
- Attachment triplet
- Character portrait, surprising contradiction
- Health score, signal counts
- Donut chart params, length distribution
- Chart JSON data (yearly trend, hourly heatmap, weekday, health trend)

### 27 HTML fragments (auto-generated)
- `hero_badges` (5-10) — from keywords + MBTI + attachment type
- `deep_analysis_body` (28 dim-rows) — 28-dim deep analysis mapped from MBTI/OCEAN/attachment/portrait data
- `ocean_bars` (5) + `ocean_details` (6) — from OCEAN Big Five
- `theatre_acts` (10) — from dialogue_theatre
- `subtext_rows` (6) — from subtext_decoder
- `mode_rows` (4) — communication mode distribution
- `topic_cloud` (6-14) — from topic_preferences
- `emotion_cards` (3) — positive/stress/baseline
- `relation_modes` (3-6) — from interaction_tips
- `timeline_rows` (4-6) — from monthly_activity timeline
- `do_items` (4) / `dont_items` (4) — from interaction_tips
- `topic_loves/neutral/avoid` — from topic_preferences
- `signal_green/yellow/red_items` (5 each) — from signals
- `best_times` (3) — from best_communication_times
- `next_predictions` (4) — from expected_next
- `ways_body` (10) — from growth_suggestions + interaction_tips
- `trajectory_cards` (3) — from trajectory
- `compat_rows` (8) — from compatibility
- `quotes_grid` (20) — from key_quotes
- `gift_rows` (5-8) — from gift_suggestions
- `growth_cards` (6) — from growth_suggestions

---

## Language handling

The tool reads UI strings from strings.json automatically based on `config.language`. The text content in sections data should match the analysis language.

---

## Reporting

The tool returns a JSON summary: `filePath`, `sizeKB`, `countWarnings`. Relay the path and size to the user.

---

## Hard constraint summary

- ❌ Generate D scalars or HTML fragments yourself (tool auto-generates)
- ❌ Read template.html / strings.json (tool does this)
- ❌ Write .py / .js / .ps1 / .sh scripts
- ❌ Write .html files (tool does this)
- ❌ Use file_operation to write reports
- ❌ Emit large HTML in your response
- ✅ Pass complete sections object (19 section keys)
- ✅ Pass stats object (message statistics)
- ✅ Ensure extract_sections has completed successfully
